<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Reserves, Debt Reported for 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2001144694 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1430 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2001144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the data provided by the Bank of 
Slovenia, our country's foreign exchange reserves amounted to 
$1.472 billion by the end of November last year. In November 
they increased by $13 million. In the same month, our country's 
foreign debt amounted to $1.801 billion. Until the end of last 
year, we paid out 333 [million] out of 1.680 billion of the 
long-term debt. This year, our country's long-term debt should 
be reduced by $481 million more. 

</TEXT>

