<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Denuclearization of Ukraine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101173794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1519 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2101173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 21 Jan--On 21 January, the Foreign Affairs 
Ministry issued the following statement to the Polish Press 
Agency: 
  "It is with great satisfaction and approval that the Foreign 
Affairs Ministry of the Polish Republic heard of the signing on 
14 January in Moscow of a three-sided agreement by the 
Presidents of the Russian Federation, the United States, and 
Ukraine. 
  President Leonid Kravchuk's decision regarding the 
denuclearization of Ukraine will have a beneficial influence on 
the security and the stability of the region, of Europe, and the 
world, despite the fact that this process is expected to take 
seven years. 
  The signing of the Moscow document opens the way to broader 
possibilities of cooperation between Ukraine and the Western 
world. 
  The Foreign Affairs Ministry of the Polish Republic 
expresses 
the hope that the concluded agreement will be implemented very 
shortly." 

</TEXT>

