<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   SLD Cites Interest in Presidential Ministries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201093394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 
GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksander Kwasniewski, leader of the Democratic 
Left Alliance [SLD], said that the coalition will continue its 
efforts to obtain deputy minister posts in three of the 
so-called presidential ministries: the Ministry of National 
Defense, the Ministry of Internal Affairs, and the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs. 
  At a meeting with parliamentary reporters, Kwasniewski also 
said, regarding ratification of the Concordat, that when there 
are just two options--yes or no--the SLD will vote against it. 
  The SLD leader also let it be known that Social Democracy 
has 
given up on the concept of the direct election of village elders 
and town and city mayors in the forthcoming local government 
elections. 

</TEXT>

