<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Opposes Pullout </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2101191094 Paris AFP in English 1837 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2101191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] London, January 21 (AFP) -- In The Hague late 
Friday [21 January] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
said he hoped London and Paris would not withdraw their troops. 
  "If they will withdraw their troops, I will have to find 
other member states who will be ready to replace them," he said. 
  "The role of the UN is to maintain peace, is to contain a 
dispute, to try to find a peaceful settlement to the dispute. 
If you just say they can continue to kill each other, I will 
say that this is an abdication," Butrus-Ghali said. 
  He also expressed confidence in EC mediator Lord Owen, whose 
replacement was demanded Thursday by the European parliament, 
and UN representative Stoltenberg. 
  "I have no criticism, on the contrary. I want to thank them 
for the wonderful work they're doing. It needs a lot of 
patience, of perseverance. I support them and express them my 
gratitude," he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

