<H3> <TI>   Britain's Hurd Addresses Troops in Vitez </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201171294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1613 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2201171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Jan 22 (TANJUG) -- British Foreign 
Secretary Douglas Hurd said on Saturday that Western allies 
faced a hard choice of whether to stay on in Bosnia or pull 
their troops out. 
  The decision to go or stay would have to be made, but not in 
the immediate future, REUTERS quotes him as saying in the 
central Bosnian town of Vitez. "It will have to be a very 
substantial weighing up process." 
  Western allies face a tough decision whether to stay in 
Bosnia saving lives and getting aid through, or to pull out, 
leaving a risk of greater savagery, said Hurd after inspecting 
the British troops near Vitez. 

</TEXT>

