<H3> <TI>   Presidency Member Urges Clinton To Bomb Serbs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301122994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1200 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with yesterday's massacre of six 
Sarajevo children in the Ali-Pasino Polje district, Ejup Ganic, 
a member of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, has sent a letter 
to U.S. President Bill Clinton. 
  The letter reads: Yesterday afternoon shells fired from Serb 
positions killed six children playing in the snow in front of 
their houses in Sarajevo. Several other children were seriously 
wounded, and doctors are still fighting for their lives. Horror 
of this kind has been going on for 22 months in the besieged 
Sarajevo. Mr. President, is there an effective way to realize 
finally your proposal on lifting the arms embargo against our 
country and on the bombing of Serb positions around Sarajevo? 
You said that you would not tolerate the strangulation of 
Sarajevo. Let us hope that your country will not allow the 
international community's stand on Bosnia-Herzegovina to 
continue being influenced by countries that tolerate genocide 
and reward aggression. 
  This is said in Ejup Ganic's letter to U.S. President Bill 
Clinton. 

</TEXT>

