<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik: Serbs Offer Unilateral Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301152494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1444 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kragujevac, 23 Jan (TANJUG)--Momcilo Krajisnik, 
president of the Srpska republic assembly, told Radio Kragujevac 
today that, in its constant efforts to restore peace, the Serb 
side would offer a so-called modus vivendi to the Croat and 
Muslim sides. 
  Explaining what that means during the "Hallmark of Time" 
program, Krajisnik said: "We bind ourselves not to take any 
military action--not even to respond to provocations, although 
that is very difficult--until 10 February. The world should see 
once again who is for war and who is for peace." 
  "We suggest that all front lines be frozen, all military 
activities halted, and relations be normalized. We are 
ready--which is yet another sacrifice on our part--to discuss 
all issues, including those that are completely clear and do not 
cause any problems for us. This is because it is very important 
to restore peace and, by lifting the sanctions, to return to 
life as it was before the war, although the victims cannot be 
brought to life," Krajisnik said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

