<H3> <TI>   Welcomes Russian Sanctions Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201184394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1719 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sarajevo, 22 Jan (TANJUG) -- We welcome the 
decision of the Duma, the lower House of the Russian parliament, 
which is demanding that Boris Yeltsin lodge an official request 
with the UN Security Council that the sanctions against the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia be lifted, said Momcilo 
Krajisnik, speaker of the assembly of the Srpska republic, to 
TANJUG correspondent Mladen Krsmanovic today. 
  "This will have far-reaching consequences, because it is 
clear now that it is the Muslim side which does not want peace. 
The formal justification for the sanctions was the war in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Thus, the sanctions can no longer remain in 
place, because the Serb side has demonstrated the maximum degree 
of cooperation and its wish to achieve peace," Krajisnik 
stressed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

