<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Attacking Serbs on `Many Fronts' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201223694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2122 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2201223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, Jan 22 (TANJUG) -- Moslem artillery and 
infantry are on Saturday attacking all Serb localities in 
Sarajevo in civil war wracked Bosnia-Herzegovina, TANJUG learns 
from Bosnian Serb Army sources. The Moslem formations appear to 
be trying, without success, to provoke a major conflict and 
blame it on the Serbs, the sources believe. 
  Moslems are attacking on many fronts throughout that former 
Yugoslav republic, TANJUG learns from the Bosnian Serb Army. 
Moslems are keeping under steady small arms and mortar fire the 
Serb localities and positions in the area of Doboj in the north, 
specifically at Gradacac and on Mts. Ozren and Vlasic. 
  Moslem assaults are continuing also in the east, in the area 
of Gorazde and along the Drina River which forms the boundary 
with Yugoslavia (Serbia/Montenegro). Moslem artillery and 
infantry have intensified operations against Foca in the 
southeast and against Serb defence lines from the directions of 
Olovo, Kladanj and Kalesija in central Bosnia. 
  Bosnian Serb Army sources say that the latest Moslem 
operations are an effort to link up the Moslem enclaves in 
Bosnia and enlarge the territory under Moslem control 
preparatory to linking up with Serbia's region of Raska 
(Sanjak), where half the population is Moslem, and then with the 
Serbian province of Kosovo-Metohija, where ethnic Albanians are 
the majority population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

