<H3> <TI>   Croats Report Attack on Zepce; Over 30 Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301191294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] It was dramatic on the Zepce front this Sunday. 
[passage omitted] 
  Over 1,000 highly destructive shells were fired today from 
tanks, 105-mm and 122-mm howitzers, and mortars deep into the 
[Croat-held] territory and on HVO [Croatian Defense Council] 
positions, and hundreds of explosive devices were also launched. 
[passage omitted] 
  Reliable reports say that 30 jihad warriors [as heard] were 
killed and seven were captured. Three members of the 111th 
Brigade and professional Andrija Tadic Brigade [both HVO] were 
killed and 12 were seriously and lightly wounded. Four 
civilians died and five were seriously wounded in the 
treacherous bombardment [as heard]. 
  Due to the heavy fighting and influx of the wounded the 
situation is dramatic in Zepce hospital. People are dying in 
the corridors and on stretchers, because Zepce has not had 
surgeons, oxygen, and other necessary resources for months. 

</TEXT>

