<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boban Demands Humanitarian Aid for Croats </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2301174194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a letter to UNHCR Sadako Ogata, Mate Boban 
demands urgent deliveries of humanitarian aid to central Bosnia, 
which has been surrounded by the Muslim army for 10 months and 
where a Muslim offensive against the Croat enclaves is under way. 
  The humanitarian situation in the area is a cause for 
concern, Boban says in his letter to the UN high commissioner, 
and adds that almost 100,000 people are facing death by 
starvation. Boban informs Sadako Ogata that in the past 50 days 
each inhabitant of the besieged Croat area in cental Bosnia has 
received less than 4 kg of food. Mate Boban goes on to accuse 
the UNHCR of not delivering humanitarian aid to the besieged 
central Bosnia populated by the Croats, since the Muslim attacks 
in the area have made the Vitez-Busovaca road impassable, and 
the UNHCR has kept silent about this. Boban also says that the 
UNHCR is resuming aid deliveries to Zenica, and that the largest 
part of the aid is taken by the Muslim army. Despite the 
promises given by the UNHCR regarding this, nothing has changed, 
Boban says, and adds that the humanitarian aid is used by the 
Muslim army to continue the war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-50120 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu015_i_94021" </HT>


