<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coposu Predicts Short Reign for Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2401181094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2401181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The future coalition government [between the Social 
Democracy Party of Romania, PDSR, and the National Romanian 
Unity Party, PUNR] will not survive more than three months, 
emphasized Corneliu Coposu, National Peasant 
Christian-Democratic Party [PNTCD] chairman, during today's 
weekly news conference. Coposu based his assertion on the fact 
that the participation of the PUNR in the new government will 
ensure the country neither stability at home nor credibility 
abroad. The PNTCD chairman also stressed the fact that, judging 
from the information he holds, the West considers the PUNR to be 
an expression of extremism that exceeds even that of the Greater 
Romania Party [PRM]. In the same context, Coposu assessed that 
the new government formula will lead to restoration and the 
blocking of reform. 
  PNTCD Spokesman Radu Vasile assessed that a situation will 
be 
created that everyone thought had been brought to an end in 1989. 
  Talking about the rejection of the opposition's offer to 
assume the responsibility of governing, the PNTCD leaders 
considered it natural that the Socialist Party of Labor [PSM] 
and the PRM will also be included in the executive, as those 
parties support the current government, our correspondent Elena 
Perdichi reports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

