<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Fails To Elect President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401213494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2057 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Jan 24 (TANJUG) -- Neither of the 
candidates nominated for the post of president of the parliament 
of the Yugoslav Republic of Serbia was returned late on Monday 
evening [24 January]. The candidate of the Socialist Party, 
Zoran Arandjelovic, secured 123 votes, two short of the 
necessary majority. The candidate nominated jointly by the 
opposition, Gvozden Rosic, was supported by 118 deputies. The 
vote was taken by 249 deputies to the 250-seat parliament. The 
procedure will be repeated on Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

