<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Stalemate' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501132194 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2501132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Serbian Assembly will resume its discussion on 
the nomination of candidates for chairman of the assembly in 
half an hour. During the recess this morning, 119 deputies of 
the Socialist Party of Serbia again proposed Zoran Arandjelovic 
as chairman of the republican parliament, while 30 Depos 
[Democratic Movement of Serbia] deputies again proposed Gvozden 
Rosic. Some deputies have expressed the view that this is a 
stalemate situation. There is a possibility of neither of the 
two candidates being elected, as was the case last night. The 
Serbian Assembly is currently in recess. The session is 
scheduled to resume at 1430. 

</TEXT>

