<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Deputies To Abstain </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401195494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1656 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the first session of the new Serbian parliament, 
the 250 deputies, 123 of whom are from the ruling Socialist 
Party of Serbia, are today expected to elect the parliament 
speaker. Before the vote, deputies discussed the candidates for 
the post of parliament speaker. "The leader of the Democratic 
Community of Vojvodina Hungarians [Demokratska Zajednica 
Vojvodjanskih Madjara -- DZVM], Andras Agoston, said that the 
Hungarians should not tip the scales and added that it would be 
best if someone from the opposition were elected as parliament 
speaker, but that the five DZVM deputies would abstain in the 
vote in parliament, not only on this issue, but also when the 
new government is voted on." 

</TEXT>

