<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rift in Democratic Prosperity `Grows Deeper' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501074494 Skopje MIC in English 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Division in PDP Grows Deeper"] </F>
  [Text] Since two days ago, there are two parallel 
leaderships of the Tetovo branch of the PDP [Party for 
Democratic Prosperity]. The first is led by Menduh Taci and the 
second is connected with the legal committee for the preparation 
of the congress of the party. The dilemma arises as to which 
leadership will be legal and present the body of the congress. 
It is interesting to note that the assembly under the 
leadership of Taci was attended by the representative of the 
Democratic Party of Albania, Saban Memia. Otherwise, 
representatives of both factions of the PDP stayed in Tirana, 
last week, on a "reconciliation" visit. However, the outcome in 
Tetovo, this weekend, shows that the "axe was not buried." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

