<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK Spokeswoman Denies Involvement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401194694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lindsay French, spokeswoman for the British UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] units, told HINA [Croatian Press Agency] 
this afternoon that the British had no connection with and were 
not responsible for a case containing ammunition and weapons 
found today aboard the Sir Geraint by Split customs officials 
during their routine inspection of cargo transported on this 
ship from Trieste yesterday. This cargo belongs to the Nordic 
battalion. They hired our ship to transport cargo from Trieste 
to Split. This is also involves a mistake in paperwork. 
UNPROFOR has admitted to this mistake and apologized for it, 
said the spokeswoman for the British UN Command stationed in 
Divulje near Split. 

</TEXT>

