<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army, NATO Agree To Hold Joint Exercises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401144394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Henning von Ondarza, commander in chief of 
NATO Allied Forces for Central Europe, today discussed in Prague 
concrete cooperation in the context of the Partnership for Peace 
plan. Gen. von Ondarza and Major General Jiri Nekvasil, chief of 
the General Staff of the Czech Army, agreed, among other things, 
that three Czech officers would attend a working meeting in 
NATO's Brussels Headquarters at the beginning of February. 
  On the basis of bilateral agreements, an exercise of a Czech 
and Dutch motorized platoons will take place in our country as 
early as in March, and an exercise of a Czech and a French 
motorized platoon will take place at the end of May and the 
beginning of June. 

</TEXT>

