<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Polls Confirms Popularity of President Gligorov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501074094 Skopje MIC in English 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Top 10 Macedonian Politicians"] </F>
  [Text] The agency for the research of pubic opinion 
BRI-MA, which cooperates with the renowned GALLUP, has conducted 
a research of the rating of the Macedonian politicians, in 
Macedonia. It was concluded that the list of the ten most 
trusted politicians is head by Kiro Gligorov with 70 percent. 
The second place belongs to Vasil Tupurkovski, who also notes a 
high rate of trust, with 50 percent of the people polled. The 
third position is occupied by the minister of the interior, 
Ljubomir Frckovski, with 50 percent, followed by Stojan Andov 
with 48 percent, and Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski with 46 
percent of the votes. Sixth on the top-list is the minister of 
defense, Vlado Popovski, seventh Foreign Minister Stevo 
Crvenkovski, eighth Petar Gosev, ninth Todor Petrov, and 10th 
Nikola Popovski. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

