<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac Seeks Assistance From UNIDO Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101153894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Following his meeting with Foreign Minister 
Jozef Moravcik and the subsequent signing of the memorandum on 
cooperation between UNIDO [United Nations Industrial Development 
Organization] and Slovakia, UNIDO Director General Mauricius de 
Maria y Campos was received this morning by Slovak President 
Michal Kovac. Jozef Rebo has the details: 
  [Rebo] [passage omitted] Slovakia is ready for bilaterally 
advantageous cooperation with UNIDO. Regarding specific matters, 
the president said that Slovakia would welcome concrete 
assistance from UNIDO, in particular in economic transformation. 
Privatization is also closely linked to economic transformation. 
We also expect assistance in putting into effect environmental 
projects and new technologies. 
  On the other hand, Slovakia wants to contribute to UNIDO 
work 
and get involved in assistance to Third World countries. We are 
able to join mining and metallurgy projects, projects in the 
construction industry, engineering, timber-processing, chemical, 
and electrotechnical industries. 
  In reply, Mr. Campos said that UNIDO respected Slovakia's 
efforts in the sphere of industrial development and that UNIDO 
wished to continue to support our efforts. [passage omitted] Mr. 
Campos then met representatives of Slovak business circles, and, 
in the afternoon, he will visit Slovak Power Engineering Works 
in Tlmace. 

</TEXT>

