<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac in Warsaw for Talks With Walesa </TI></H3>
<H4>   Walesa Welcomes Kovac </H4>
<F P=102> LD2501114294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1039 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 25 Jan--On 25 January, President Lech Walesa 
welcomed to the Belweder Slovak President Michal Kovac, who is 
on his first official visit to Poland. The Sejm and senate 
speakers and the prime minster took part in the ceremony. 
  After the welcoming ceremony, both presidents began 
face-to-face talks. After this meeting, plenary talks will be 
held between the two delegations. A PAP journalist has learned 
unofficially that the agreements on regional cooperation and 
environmental protection will most probably not be signed. 
Representatives of the Polish Ministry of Foreign Affairs had 
announced before that such agreements were to be signed. 

</TEXT>

