<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovac in Warsaw for Talks With Walesa </TI></H3>
<H4>   Expected Agreements Not Signed </H4>
<F P=102> LD2501163994 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1536 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 25 Jan--Presidents Lech Walesa and Michal 
Kovac did not sign, as announced earlier, Polish-Slovak 
agreements on transborder and regional cooperation and on 
environmental protection. 
  As Wladyslaw Klaczynski, head of the Foreign Ministry Press 
and Information Department, explained, the agreements had not 
been signed for "technical reasons." The Slovak side put 
forward additional suggestions to the prepared agreements. 
Klaczynski announced that the agreements "would be signed in 
the immediate future." 
  A Polish-Slovak agreement on investment protection and on 
avoiding double taxation is also in the final phase of 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

