<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak To Visit Brussels, Meet EC Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401172694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1641 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Jan--Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak will 
pay a working visit to Brussels on 2-3 February. During the 
visit, the government press office reports, he will meet NATO 
General Secretary Manfred Woerner; Jacques Delors, president of 
the European Commission; Egon Klepsch, speaker of the European 
Parliament; W. van Eekelen, secretary general of the Western 
European Union; and Jean-Luc Dehaene, prime minister of Belgium. 
  The chairman of the Council of Ministers will also take part 
in a conference organized under the auspices of the Center of 
International Strategic Studies devoted to the future 
cooperation between Poland and the European Communities and 
NATO. A meeting with Poles living abroad is also expected. 

</TEXT>

