<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Visit Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501120394 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1105 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia, has postponed for a few days the 
date of his arrival in Poland. Janusz Bryczkowski, who invited 
Zhirinovskiy to Poland, told AFP that his guest will arrive in 
Poland not on Thursday but on Sunday [30 January] because of a 
visit to Belgrade, which had not been planned earlier. 
  Bryczkowski said in a telephone conversation last night that 
Zhirinovskiy expressed his concern about the lack of guarantees 
from the Polish authorities concerning his security during the 
visit to our country. 

</TEXT>

