<H3> <TI>   World Bank Talks With Polish Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401181994 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1642 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 24 Jan--Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz, the deputy 
prime minister and justice minister, this afternoon received 
World Bank representative Kemal Dervis. During the meeting, 
officials from the Ministries of Health, Education, and Labor 
briefed the guest on how the credits were used and on the 
possible future needs of the ministries. 
  This morning the head of the World Bank mission met Marek 
Borowski, the deputy prime minister and finance minister, and 
Hanna Gronkiewicz-Waltz, the president of the Polish National 
Bank. During the meeting with the deputy prime minister, Dervis 
announced that a World Bank mission will come to Poland in March 
to review the existing loans and to discuss loans under 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

