<F P=102>  LD2401225194 Warsaw PAP in English 2239 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2401225194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Washington, Jan. 24 -- Foreign Minister Andrzej 
Olechowski met Deputy Secretary of State designate Strobe 
Talbott in Washington on Monday [24 January] for talks lasting 
45 minutes. After the meeting Olechowski said that Poland would 
be the first country of Central and Eastern Europe to be visited 
by a western delegation of technical experts in order to prepare 
the ground for Polands participation in NATOs "Partnership for 
Peace" programme for cooperation with those countries. 
Olechowski said the mission would probably arrive in Poland 
next week. Olechowski had arrived in Washington on Sunday 
evening to hold a series of talks with representatives of the 
Clinton administration and congressmen on Monday and Tuesday. 
  Meeting with U.S. politicians, Olechowski is expected to 
discuss such key issues as Poland's participation in the 
"Partnership for Peace" programme, security and Polish-U.S. 
bilateral relations. From Washington Olechowski is scheduled to 
go on a tour of four U.S. cities to meet with businessmen whom 
he will try to encourage to do business with Polish partners. 

</TEXT>

