<H3> <TI>   PUNR Endorses Protocol </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2201203394 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1701 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2201203394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 22/1/1994 -- The National 
Council of the Romanian National Unity Party [PUNR] discussed on 
January 22 the results of the negotiations conducted between the 
PUNR and the Party of Social Democracy of Romania [PDSR] 
regarding the PUNR offer to participate in the government, as 
well as the content of the draft protocol articulated to that 
end, reads a release issued to the national agency ROMPRES by 
the PUNR National Council. 
  The National Council endorses the protocol provisions, 
considering them to be the minimal condition for the PUNR 
participation in the government. If the PDSR fails to apply the 
provisions of the respective protocol, the PUNR will withdraw 
its parliamentary backing of the current government. 
  The PUNR National Council considers that the PUNR 
participation in the government is a major political decision of 
a nature to redeem to the nation the confidence and hope for the 
country's economic recovery and the improvement of the social 
life, giving the act of governing more authoritativeness, 
dynamism, competence, responsibility, the release reads. 

