<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kenan Criticizes DPS `Cooperation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2101194094 Sofia KONTINENT in Bulgarian 19 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2101194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia KONTINENT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, 18 January -- In cooperation with the 
Rights and Freedoms Movement [DPS], Bulgarians want to eliminate 
the Turkish presence in Bulgaria, Adem Kenan, chairman of the 
Turkish Democratic Party [TDP], and his first deputy Emin Hamdi 
claim in an extensive interview given to the Turkish ORTADOGU 
daily, BTA reports. In addition to the interview, the daily 
also published an "Open Letter to the State Leadership of the 
Republic of Bulgaria from the Leadership of the TDP in Bulgaria." 
  Kenan and Hamdi level criticisms against certain DPS 
leaders, 
accusing them of cooperation with the KGB and the Bulgarian 
special services. At the same time, the leaders of the 
unregistered TDP show concern for the fate of the Khazar Turks 
and Muslims living in Georgia. According to them, there is a 
high likelihood and risk of the Georgians applying "the 
Bulgarian model of assimilation." 

</TEXT>

