  [Excerpt] Knin, 25 Jan (TANJUG) -- Milan Martic has been 
elected president of the republic of Serb Krajina, the third 
since its founding. According to the official figures of the 
Republican Election Commission in last Sunday's election Martic 
won 104,234 and Milan Babic, the other candidate 97,377 votes. 
