<F P=102>  AU2501154894 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1430 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2501154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian rightist leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, 
president and deputy of the Liberal Democratic Party, will 
arrive in Slovenia on Thursday [27 January]. We have learned 
that Zhirinovskiy has officially applied for the entry visa, 
which he will also be granted. For the time being it is not 
known whether the Slovene politicians have coordinated their 
views about this visit. In connection with the claim that 
Zhirinovskiy has allegedly sent a letter to some Slovene 
political institutions informing them of the visit, the Foreign 
Ministry says that this is not the case and that the Foreign 
Ministry has received no such letter. Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is 
expected to remain in Slovenia until 1 February. He will be 
staying in Bled where he will be joined by sympathizers from all 
over Europe. 

