<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDSR Approves Coalition Formula </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701090294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0500 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Central Executive Bureau of the PDSR 
[Social Democracy Party of Romania] held a meeting yesterday, 
which was attended by Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu, other 
ministers, and PDSR members. [passage omitted] 
  At the end of the meeting, PDSR President Adrian Nastase 
made 
a brief statement to the press. He mentioned that discussions 
regarding the negotiations with the parties that form the 
majority in parliament were very heated. After four hours, the 
Central Executive Bureau unanimously approved the formula of a 
coalition government open to all parties that belong to the 
current parliamentary majority. Adrian Nastase said that this 
act should be preceded by the preparation of a draft political 
pact open to all parties, as well as a political understanding 
between all five parties -- namely the PDSR, PUNR [Romanian 
National Unity Party], the PRM [Greater Romania Party], the PSM 
[Socialist Party of Labor], and the PDAR [Romanian Democratic 
Agrarian Party]. 
  Likewise, Adrian Nastase mentioned that it is necessary to 
achieve a consensus on an anticrisis and anti-inflation program. 
After its drafting, consultations will continue with a view to 
setting up a parliamentary coalition government by 1 March. 
  Mr. Adrian Nastase also expressed his surprise that these 
elements discussed with the aforementioned parties on 21 January 
in the evening were not taken into consideration at the meeting 
of the PUNR National Council. Mr. Adrian Nastase also stressed 
that the Central Executive Bureau wants to reaffirm the 
willingness of the PDSR for a political dialogue with the 
parliamentary parties in the opposition, noting that this 
dialogue might take place at the end of the next week. 
  Referring to the memorandum convened between the Romanian 
Government and the IMF, Mr. Nastase informed the correspondents 
present that the participants in the meeting of the Central 
Executive Bureau agreed unanimously that it is necessary for the 
parliament to adopt a declaration in which it expresses support 
for this memorandum as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

