<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Miners Strike Grows; 65,000 Stop Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601133894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2601133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The labor conflict begun by the Rovinari Federation 
of Free Trade Unions has spread, practically speaking, 
throughout the coal mining region administered by the Targu Jiu 
Autonomous Lignite Public Corporation, our correspondent Titus 
Stoichitoiu reports. Over 65,000 employees have stopped work, 
the only departments still functioning being those that 
transport personnel inside the pits and deliver coal to the 
population. 
  Another warning strike and a rally was announced today by 
employees of the Targu Jiu [mining equipment] Repair Plant. 
Similarly, the Lignite Mining Trade Union Confederation, which 
is affiliated to the union confederation headed by Miron Cosma 
[union leader of the Jiu Valley miners], requested permission to 
organize a rally at Rovinari, but the local police and mayor's 
office refused, suggesting that it should be postponed until 
after the general strike in the region. 

</TEXT>

