<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SRI Head Talks With Chinese on Drugs, Crime </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601100794 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 22 Jan 
94 p 8 </F>

<F P=103> AU2601100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dan Damian report: "Virgil Magureanu Holds Talks With the </F>
Chinese Intelligence Service on the Asian Drug Dealer Networks"] 
  [Text] Virgil Magureanu, director of the SRI [Romanian 
Intelligence Service], has been to Beijing, China over the past 
week. Being there at the invitation of China's public security 
minister, Magureanu held a series of talks with representatives 
of the Chinese intelligence service aimed at sharing information 
gathered by the two intelligence services in an effort to combat 
drug trafficking. 
  Another goal of the visit is related to the fact that since 
1989 Romania, like other Eastern European countries, has been 
facing a crime wave in which Asians are also involved and some 
of these violations could also threaten Romania's national 
security. 
  The SRI director, carrying a (black) Romanian diplomatic 
passport, left for Beijing on a TAROM [Romanian national 
airline] charter flight. 

</TEXT>

