<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Court To Begin Trial of Ethnic Albanians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2601192494 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2601192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Serbian Court of Prishtina District is expected 
to begin the trial of 19 Albanians who are charged with 
allegedly creating the organizations "National Movement for the 
Republic of Kosova" and "National Movement for the Liberation of 
Kosova." They are also charged with hostile activity in 
infringing the territorial integrity. 
  The trial has been postponed four times so far. Such trials, 
more of which are expected to be trumped-up in the future, aim 
to frighten Albanians and encourage them to leave Kosova. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

