<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Granic Letter to Kinkel on Refugee Problem </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601224494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 2203 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601224494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mr. Granic sent a letter to the German Vice 
Chancellor and Foreign Minister, Klaus Kinkel, following 
Germany's decision to repatriate Croat refugees in Germany 
starting from the 30 April of this year. 
  The Croatian foreign minister thanked Germany for its 
efforts 
in caring for thousands of Croat refugees but pointed out that 
one-third of Croatia's territory was still under occupation so 
that most of the refugees cannot return to their homes. 
  In his letter Mr. Granic called on Germany to help in the 
return of refugees to their homes but urged it to keep in mind 
that this process should be carried out in phases in accordance 
with the normalization of relations and the reintegration of the 
UN-protected areas into Croatia's legal system. 

</TEXT>

