<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Agrees on Administratative Setup </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601205394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 2000 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] At its session in the Kolodeje district of Prague 
today, the Czech Government reached an agreement on general 
principles of one single document on the concept of the reform 
of the territorial administrative setup. This was announced by 
Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus at the end of the session. He 
added that there was no fundamental dispute among the four 
coalition parties about the powers of the higher-level 
territorial administrative entities. The ministers agreed, 
above all, on powers to be transferred from central bodies to 
regional bodies and on the principle that regional 
self-administration bodies would not deprive villages of their 
current powers. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

