<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats Report `Vicious' Muslim Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601213494 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] After launching a vicious attack this morning 
from the direction of Maglaj against positions held by the 
Croatian Defense Council [HVO] in the area of Lijesnica and 
Cehajic, the Muslim army mounted a combined artillery and 
infantry assault in the area of Dolina from the direction of 
Zavidovici. 
  After three hours of ferocious fighting, members of the 
(Marko Praljic) battalion managed to disperse the enemy army. 
Three Muslim soldiers, including one Iranian mojahid, were 
killed on this occasion and their bodies have remained on the 
territory controlled by the HVO. A considerable quantity of 
arms was captured as well. 
  At noon the Muslims began an attack in the region of Brezova 
Kosa and Krsic from the direction of Zeljezno Polje in the 
western sector of the Zepce front. The fighting is still under 
way and the defenders are repelling all the aggressor's attacks. 
  The most difficult situation today is on the Maglaj front. 
After repulsing an attempted infantry spearhead into Croat 
villages in the Bosna river valley near Maglaj, members of the 
Zepce brigade launched a counterattack and succeeded in taking a 
very important strategic point from which their firepower can 
control access to the Natronka factory where the Muslims have 
been manufacturing arms for quite some time now. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

