<H3> <TI>   Slovak President Continues Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Economic Issues Discussed </H4>
<F P=102> LD2501195894 Warsaw PAP in English 1907 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2501195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Jan. 25 -- President of the Slovak Republic 
Michal Kovac on Tuesday afternoon received Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak. "We have discussed economic issues and the 
results of these talks are very significant," Michal Kovac told 
reporters after the meeting. "We have agreed that Prime 
Minister Pawlak would come to Bratislava and that our 
governments will meet in their full composition," Kovac said. 
  During the "Visegrad group summit" in Prague Waldemar Pawlak 
and Prime Minister Vaclav Meciar agreed that prior to a meeting 
of both cabinets, economic ministers of both countries will meet 
to assess the progress in preparation of agreements between both 
republics. 
  Commenting upon the decision to postpone the signing of 
agreements between Poland and Slovakia, the prime minister said 
that "it is worth to devote more time to these agreements to 
prepare them better." 
  Pawlak stressed that it would be good for the cooperation 
between Poland and Slovakia to be more concrete. "The problem 
boils down not to documents and agreements but above all to 
direct contacts of many people," the prime minister said. 

</TEXT>

