<H3> <TI>   Three Poles Face Smuggling Charges in Ukraine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701105894 Warsaw PAP in English 2046 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Jan. 26 -- Three Polish citizens are 
currently facing trial in Ukraine on charges of smuggling, and 
one of them has allegedly confessed to working with the Polish 
security services, a well-informed source close to the Polish 
Government told the Polish press agency PAP today. 
  The source suggested that it was most likely that the trial 
of the Poles, which begins next Monday [31 January] in the 
Ukrainian capital Kiev, is intended to act as a counter to the 
trial in Warsaw on spying charges of Ukrainian security service 
officer Anatoliy Lysenko, which started in Warsaw on January 19. 
  Neither the Polish Foreign Ministry, nor the State 
Protection 
Office (UOP), was prepared to confirm a statement on Tuesday [25 
January] from the press bureau of the Ukrainian Foreign Ministry 
that Polish-Ukrainian discussions on the Lysenko affair were 
held on January 24. 

