<F P=101> Yugoslavia: Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Prosperity Assembles in Gostivar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2501175494 Tirana ATA in English 1119 GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2501175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, January 25 (ATA) -- The third election 
assembly of the Democratic Prosperity Party [DPP], the branch of 
Gostivar, was held on January 24, 1994, this branch reports. 
Taking part in this assembly were: the representative of the 
Albanian Democratic Party, Shaban Memia, deputy of Albanian 
parliament, representatives of the branches Karshiake, Qender, 
and Gazi Babe from Skopje, and of the branches Tetove, Struge, 
Manastir, Diber, Kercove. The assembly called for holding of a 
unique congress according to the agreement reached in Tirana 
between representatives of the Provisional Leading Council and 
representatives of the group of the DPP. The assembly also 
emphasized that the DPP belongs to no one, therefore it should 
not be instrumentalized. Attending the assembly were 
representatives from 46 sub-branches out of 48 that are 
altogether. 
  Participants in the assembly elected delegates to the 
untimely congress, the members of the central assembly and the 
new presidency of the branch. Refik Dauti was elected chairman. 

</TEXT>

