<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakovski Officers Legion Denies TRUD Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701201394 Sofia BULGARSKA ARMIYA in Bulgarian 21 Jan 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BULGARSKA ARMIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [BULGARSKA ARMIYA staff report: "The Rakovski Officers </F>
Legion Respects the Law and Does Not Interfere With Politics"] 
  [Text] Major Rusi Gochev, chairman of the Bulgarian 
Rakovski Officers Legion, has sent a letter to Dr. Zhelyu Zhelev 
and to Minister of Defense Valentin Aleksandrov, which reads as 
follows: 
  "On 7 January 1994 the daily TRUD published a report under 
the headline: `Presidential Advisers Reach for the Army' in 
which our organization is mentioned among other things. 
  "After thorough investigations and numerous interviews, we 
officially declare that neither our leadership nor individual 
member-clubs of the Legion have ever commented on the 
president's letter to the commanders of the Armed Forces' 
branches, or on the relations between the president's Military 
Office and the Army's General Staff. 
  "We are convinced that the aforementioned report has cited 
the Legion in a deliberately distorted fashion, prompted by 
evidently biased political intentions. 
  "Similar `operations' are likely to provoke tension among 
our 
members. They are contributing to a politicization of the 
soldiers' life which is counterproductive to the consolidation 
of the Bulgarian Army's fighting ability." 

</TEXT>

