<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Public Has `Highest Confidence' in Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701181794 Sofia BULGARSKA ARMIYA in Bulgarian 24 Jan 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BULGARSKA ARMIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [BULGARSKA ARMIYA staff report: "Army Once Again Enjoys </F>
Highest Confidence"] 
  [Text] According to a poll conducted this month by 
BBSS-Gallup International, 69 percent of the respondents have 
confidence in the Bulgarian Army. The result indicates a 
traditionally high level of popularity, one that cannot be 
achieved by other institutions or any individual in Bulgaria! 
  The president, who enjoys the confidence of 49 percent of 
the 
respondents, continues to lead the list of politicians, followed 
by Aleksandur Tomov, Georgi Pirinski, and Lyuben Berov. The 
police maintain the popularity figure of 43 percent that they 
reached at the end of last year. Of those polled, 27 percent 
have faith in the government, while parliament's rating 
continues to be low -- only 12 percent. Despite this, more than 
half of the 19 most popular politicians are National Assembly 
deputies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

