<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Andruta Ceausescu To Be Released </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701192494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today the Bucharest Territorial Military Court 
accepted the application of Andruta Ceausescu [brother of former 
dictator Nicolae Ceausescu], requesting that he should be 
released from jail for health reasons. 
  The judges decided to set Ceausescu free for the next six 
months, considering that he is suffering from illnesses that 
cannot be cured within the penitentiary system. 
  The ROMPRES news agency reminds us that, in his capacity as 
commander of the Baneasa school of Romania's Ministry of 
Interior, in December 1989 Andruta Ceausescu participated in the 
repression of demonstrators, after which he was sentenced to 15 
years imprisonment and reducing to the ranks, for attempted 
aggravated murder and the instigation of genocide. 

</TEXT>

