<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coposu Predicts Short Life for New Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701185894 Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER in Romanian 25 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Corneliu Coposu, president of the National </F>
Peasant Christian Democratic Party, at a news conference in 
Bucharest on 24 January: "Mr. Coposu Warns: The Men in Power 
Will Be Kicked Out of Their Jobs Within 24 Hours of the Change 
of Regime!] 
  [Text] "The new government will agonize for a maximum 
three months after its creation. We do not give the new 
government, if it is created, more than three months to 
survive," Mr. Corneliu Coposu, president of the National Peasant 
Christian Democratic Party [PNTCD] said at a news conference 
yesterday. "This is a very short-term transitional government. 
According to our information, not even Mr. Ion Iliescu likes 
the idea of the Romanian National Unity Party [PUNR] joining the 
cabinet, since he is aware of the image as an extremist party 
that the PUNR 'enjoys' abroad. The new team will cause negative 
reactions and will be contested from the very start. The new 
ministers might not even obtain the endorsement of the 
parliament, although I do not see why the power should be afraid 
of that, since its holds the majority there... Anyhow, it is a 
strong proof of naivete on the part of the people in power to 
believe that, if they occupy all the decision-taking functions 
in the current society, they will stay nailed to their chairs. 
Actually, all these newly appointed people will be kicked out of 
their jobs within 24 hours of the change of regime..." 
  He also said that Romania risks being ejected from the 
Council of Europe if the government does not implement the nine 
amendments imposed by the aforementioned body within a maximum 
of six months from the date of adherence. A similar situation 
will occur if the former owners do not get back the assets 
confiscated by the communists and sue the Romanian state at the 
Council of Europe. "It is certain that the owners will win 
their cases and the restitution verdicts will have to be applied 
immediately," the PNTCD leader said. "Without foreign 
financing, the government will get bogged down in petty 
administrative activities, which will also be blocked themselves 
by the lack of money. But what is worse, I have yet to hear of 
a program from either the PUNR or the Social Democracy Party of 
Romania [PDSR]; their so-called salvation programs are nothing 
but fantasies. We have never considered Mr. Nicolae Vacaroiu to 
be an authentic prime minister, but rather a candidate for the 
position." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-50341 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu019_y_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-019 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

