<H3> <TI>   Cost of Living Increases by 13 Percent in Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701181894 Skopje MIC in English 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Consumer Basket For January"] </F>
  [Text] According to the calculations of the Republic 
Bureau for the Advancement of the Household, the January 
consumer basket is some 12.4 percent more expensive than the 
December one, while the December figure is 13 percent higher 
than in November. In November last year 4,970 denars were 
needed for the minimum required food for a four member family, 
in December 5,799, while during the first months of this year 
this figure rose to 6,519 denars. The price of the consumer 
basket is constantly rising and during the period 
January-December its value increased 2.5 times, that is, 276 
percent. The January basket on the other hand compared to the 
same last years has increased 300 percent. The indicators used 
to show this increase are the price increases of the milk, 
pastas, bread and the 11 percent increase in the price of milk. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

