<F P=102>  AU2701211894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 2000 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a session of the Macedonian Parliament today, a 
deputy from the Albanian Party of Democratic Prosperity [name 
indistinct] accused the VMRO-DPMNE [Internal Macedonian 
Revolutionary Organization-Party of Macedonian National Unity] 
of following an anti-Macedonian policy. He claimed that members 
of the VMRO-DPMNE leadership frequently visited Bulgaria and 
obtained large amounts of money from there. 
  In reply to the charges, Dosta Dimovska, deputy chairman of 
the VMRO-DPMNE, accused the Albanian party, asserting that its 
leaders often travel to Albania to receive instructions and 
that, in practice, they place themselves at the service of a 
foreign state. 
  Stojan Andov, chairman of the Macedonian Parliament, offered 
his services as an arbitrator. He declared that Macedonia is a 
democratic state and everyone can travel anywhere he or she 
likes, but that people's deputies must conduct themselves in 
word and deed in their country's interests. 

</TEXT>

