<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajina Serbs Protest Albright Article </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2701173294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1346 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2701173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 27 Jan (TANJUG) -- The Foreign Ministry 
of the republic of Serb Krajina sent a letter today to all 
diplomatic and consular missions in Belgrade, warning that the 
text carried by the 24 January newsletter of the U.S. Embassy in 
Belgrade was written in the spirit of the falsehoods concocted 
by the Croatian propaganda headquarters. 
  The letter, also forwarded to TANJUG, says that by writing 
the article in the US embassy's newsletter, Madeleine Albright 
-- the U.S. ambassador to the United Nations -- had "abused the 
hospitality of the Serbian people and overstepped the norms of 
diplomatic conduct" because she called on "all countries to help 
the war crimes tribunal." 
  The text implies that "the Ovcara mass grave near Vukovar 
contains evidence about Serbian crimes against the Croats -- 
something the European civilization of the 20th Century ought to 
be ashamed of." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

