<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Arrives for `Private' Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2701194594 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1800 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The leader of the Russian nationalist Liberal 
Democratic Party, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, arrived to Brnik 
airport after a one-hour delay this afternoon. The mere 
announcement of his arrival received considerable attention in 
the domestic and international media. The controversial Russian 
politician is paying a private visit to our country. 
Immediately upon his arrival he left for Bled. He will be 
staying in Portoroz tomorrow and Sunday, and on Monday he is 
supposed to visit Serbia. 

</TEXT>

