<H3> <TI>   Party Invites Izetbegovic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2601174494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2601174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National-Social Alliance of Slovenia [NSSS] last 
night sent an invitation to Alija Izetbegovic to visit Slovenia 
and meet Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, president of the Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia, who will be in Slovenia from 27 to 
31 January, the Slovene press agency reports. The NSSS, which 
had originally invited Zhirinovskiy to Slovenia, announced that 
he would put forward new proposals for the settlement of the 
crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Slovene Foreign Ministry 
today denied, in a statement for HINA, reports that Liberal 
Democratic Party Leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy will meet Slovene 
Foreign Minister Lojze Peterle during his visit to Slovenia. 
The Foreign Ministry said that Zhirinovskiy's visit to 
Ljubljana is private and that no meetings with any official 
bodies are scheduled. 

</TEXT>

