<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Walesa Receives Knesset Speaker </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2801114594 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1039 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2801114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 28 Jan--President Lech Walesa today received 
Israel's Knesset Speaker Shevah Weiss, who has been on a 
parliamentary visit to Poland. 
  Weiss handed the president a letter from Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin, in which he recalls the importance of 
the visit to Israel by Lech Walesa and underscores that Poland 
occupies an important place in Europe. Prime Minister Rabin 
writes that everything connected with the known 
Israeli-Palestinian declaration is most important in Israeli 
policy. 
  During talks in the Belweder Palace, reference was also made 
to history and the contemporary issues of both states and the 
world. President Walesa said that Poland is presented so far as 
a cemetery of our (Polish and Jewish) nations. He called for 
looking into the future and focusing on the youth and their 
upbringing. He also underscored that Poland is a victim of the 
betrayal by "the great of this world." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

