<F P=102>  AU2701204394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2701204394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bosnia-Herzegovina Government held a session 
today that addressed the privatization of the social property. 
The government believes that the identification of all social 
property should be carried out with the aim of its 
privatization. At the end of the open part of the session, 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic informed all 
present that there are indications that major Croatian Army 
forces are concentrated on the Bosnia-Herzegovina territory, 
around Prozor, to be precise. He proposed that the government 
requests additional information about the presence of the 
Croatian Armed Forces on Bosnia-Herzegovina soil to facilitate a 
decision about further measures, that is to say, that the 
government could decide in the course of tomorrow whether to 
demand an urgent session of the UN Security Council. 

</TEXT>

